review_blob: Light, floral and easy to drink. Not overly hoppy, citrus hop definitely present. Quite lively, lingers a touch on the palate.
beer_name: Dancing Duck Ay Up / Ey Up

review_blob: Slightly cloudy cider. 6.0% and slightly drier than the medium-dry billing. Very drinkable and not offensive, clean finish.
beer_name: Mr Whiteheads Heart Of Hampshire Cider

review_blob: Golden in colour, light, hoppy, with the aroma and sweetness from the elderflower. A marvellous pint that you could drink all day...
Very dark ruby in colour. Not masses of flavour. Light, clean and somewhat dry finish.
